This query targets behavioral indicators associated with Salt Typhoon-style intrusions, which typically emphasize:

VPN / edge device compromise (initial access pivot)
Credential harvesting and reuse
Internal reconnaissance at low volume
Stealthy lateral movement using legitimate tools
Long dwell time with minimal noisy malware
Authentication anomalies across time and geography

This hunt focuses on identity + lateral movement + edge access behavior, rather than malware signatures.



index=auth OR index=security OR index=vpn OR index=proxy
(
    EventCode=4624 OR EventCode=4625 OR EventCode=4768 OR EventCode=4769 OR EventCode=4776
)
| eval is_success=if(EventCode=4624,1,0)
| eval is_fail=if(EventCode=4625,1,0)

| eval is_vpn=if(match(Logon_Process,"vpn|radius|citrix|fortinet|checkpoint"),1,0)

| eval is_suspicious_logon=case(
    is_vpn=1 AND is_success=1, "VPN Successful Login",
    is_fail=1, "Failed Authentication Activity",
    Logon_Type=3, "Network Logon",
    Logon_Type=10, "RDP Login"
)

| stats 
    count as total_events
    sum(is_success) as successes
    sum(is_fail) as failures
    dc(src_ip) as unique_ips
    dc(host) as unique_hosts
    values(is_suspicious_logon) as behaviors
    by user src_ip dest host

| where failures > 10 OR unique_hosts > 3 OR unique_ips > 5
| sort - failures
